  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Accommodation Centers for Unaccompanied Migrant Children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this project is to set up and operate Emergency Accommodation Centres in mainland Greece. These facilities will operate as a first step to provide assistance to unaccompanied migrant children (UMC) identified in precarious living conditions and to organize their safe and timely referral to other care arrangements, on the basis of an individualized assessment of the child&apos;s needs and best interests. In this manner, the Emergency Accommodation Centers will constitute the first point of contact between the UMC and child protection professionals, as an IOM multi-sectorial team of high-skilled and experienced staff will be deployed to ensure that children&apos;s needs, background, best interests and future aspirations are comprehensively assessed, recorded and communicated to relevant actors. It is envisaged that through the set-up of the Emergency Accommodation Centers, 200 places will be created in the Greek mainland at urban and rural areas.</narrative>
  </description>
